## Purpose

Enforce use of `Tag` and `OLQTag` components for all status indicators and percentage-coded labels. Never use manual styled divs with inline color logic.

## Rules

- ALWAYS import `Tag` from `@/components/ui/tag` for status labels, categories, and attributes
- ALWAYS import `OLQTag` from `@/components/ui/olq-tag` for percentage-coded quality indicators
- NEVER write a custom `getXStyle()` function that returns inline background/color/border values
- NEVER use `className="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded"` with inline styles for status display
- NEVER hard-code the OLQ color thresholds â€” they are built into `OLQTag`

## Quick Check

```tsx
// WRONG â€” custom styled div with inline color function
const getOLQStyle = (olq: string) => {
  const pct = parseFloat(olq);
  if (pct < 50) return { backgroundColor: '#FBD0CC', color: '#EA1100' };
  // ...
};
<div className="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded" style={getOLQStyle(item.olq)}>
  {item.olq}
</div>

// CORRECT â€” OLQTag handles all threshold logic internally
import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';
<OLQTag percentage={85} />

// WRONG â€” custom span for a status label
<span style={{ background: '#eaf3e6', color: '#2a8703', padding: '2px 8px' }}>Active</span>

// CORRECT â€” Tag with semantic variant
import { Tag } from '@/components/ui/tag';
<Tag variant="success">Active</Tag>
```

## Tag Component

**Import**: `import { Tag } from '@/components/ui/tag';`

**Variants**: `default` | `primary` | `secondary` | `success` | `warning` | `destructive` | `info`

**Sizes**: `sm` | `md` | `lg`

**Optional props**: `dismissible`, `onClick`, `icon`, `disabled`

```tsx
<Tag variant="success" size="md">Active</Tag>
<Tag variant="warning" size="sm">Pending</Tag>
<Tag variant="destructive">Rejected</Tag>
<Tag variant="info" dismissible onDismiss={() => {}}>Filter</Tag>
```

## OLQTag Component

**Import**: `import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';`

**Built-in threshold logic** (do not replicate externally):

| Range | Color | Tokens |
|-------|-------|--------|
| < 50% | Red | `--ld-semantic-color-fill-accent-red-subtle` / `--ld-semantic-color-text-accent-red` |
| 50â€“79% | Yellow | `--ld-semantic-color-fill-accent-spark-subtle` / `--ld-semantic-color-text-accent-spark` |
| >= 80% | Green | `--ld-semantic-color-fill-accent-green-subtle` / `--ld-semantic-color-text-accent-green` |

```tsx
// Pass a numeric percentage â€” OLQTag picks the color automatically
<OLQTag percentage={42} />   // red
<OLQTag percentage={65} />   // yellow
<OLQTag percentage={92} />   // green
```

## Migration Pattern

When you find a manual OLQ styled div in any page:

1. Remove the `getOLQStyle` function (or equivalent inline style logic)
2. Add `import { OLQTag } from '@/components/ui/olq-tag';`
3. Replace `<div style={getOLQStyle(item.olq)}>{item.olq}</div>` with `<OLQTag percentage={parseFloat(item.olq)} />`
4. Delete any leftover Tailwind color utilities used only by the old pattern

## Enforcement

Find violations:

```bash
# Find manual OLQ/status style functions
grep -r "getOLQStyle\|getStatusStyle\|getColorForPct" client/pages/ client/components/

# Find inline-styled status divs
grep -r "backgroundColor.*EA1100\|backgroundColor.*FBD0CC\|backgroundColor.*#[0-9a-fA-F]\{6\}" client/pages/
```

